[Student "S"]
{Here SOUTH has the kind of hand you need to raise a preempt to game.

SOUTH assumes that NORTH has a hand with six winners in it. He can provide four more, so 
that is just enough for game. He bids 4\H.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "2"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "NS"]
[Deal "E:AQJ9765.QT2.7.63 82.A963.AK53.985 K4.KJ5.942.KQJ72 T3.874.QJT86.AT4"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "4S"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "E"]
1S pass 2C pass 2S pass 4S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 2, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "400ed683cdb61f9116120154633a28eccc9e5e018dabae580a788276de611e40"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/weak_twos"]
[Student "S"]
{EAST has a 7-card \S suit but he is too strong to open with a preemptive bid. 
So he opens 1\S instead.

WEST should respond 2\C, and EAST can do nothing but rebid the \S suit.

WEST thinks there should be game and bids 4\S}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
[Dealer "S"]
[Vulnerable "EW"]
[Deal "S:764.AK9743.72.Q5 JT9532.82.943.A6 KQ.QJ.AKQ65.KJ42 A8.T65.JT8.T9873"]
[Declarer "S"]
[Contract "4H"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "S"]
2H pass 4H pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: S, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:2, nBasis: 0, nRot: 2, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "3a43aabbc918e60114c979755fcbaa9f8c3e6294f97be1afbe725414d636d9d6"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/weak_twos"]
[Student "S"]
{SOUTH is too weak to open 1\H but just right for 2\H.

Wow! NORTH has 21 HCP and two good \Hs. Could this be time for a slam try?

Nope, no slam here. Suppose SOUTH has six \Hs headed by the AK. The trump suit 
would certainly be solid, but then SOUTH couldn't possibly have an outside Ace as well or he would have been 
too strong for a Weak-two opening. So NORTH just bids 4\H.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "4"]
[Dealer "W"]
[Vulnerable "All"]
[Deal "W:J83.KQJ762.85.85 T97.AT983.AT3.T3 AQ5.4.KQ94.KJ742 K642.5.J762.AQ96"]
[Declarer "W"]
[Contract "2H"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "W"]
2H pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 4, chOption: W, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:3, nBasis: 2, nRot: 1, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "5f9bbf8354184f269b451eb4116009277aa04a6a03de2537950bb7d84d1c5c5e"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/weak_twos"]
[Student "S"]
{EAST really hates that 2\H opening by WEST.

But there's no sense bidding and probably making matters worse, so she grits her 
teeth and passes.

If you think 3NT has a chance you are delusional.}

